# Salyan, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Salyan (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Ispiksky Selsoviet, Suleyman-Stalsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. Population:  There are 2 streets.
Geography
Salyan is located  southeast of Makhachkala and  southeast of Kasumkent (the district's administrative centre) by road. Ispik is the nearest rural locality.
